// Evolution cutscene Yarn nodes.
// These are placeholder stubs. In a future session the actual cutscene visuals
// (3D model → 2D sprite transform animation) will be triggered via Yarn commands
// defined in a dedicated CutsceneDirector.cs.
//
// To add a new evolution cutscene:
//   1. Duplicate the Evolve_Template node below.
//   2. Set the title to match CharacterData.evolutionYarnNode on the asset.
//   3. Replace the dialogue text with character-specific flavour text.
//   4. Add <<startCutscene>> / <<endCutscene>> commands when CutsceneDirector is built.

title: Evolve_Template
---
// <<startCutscene>>   ← slot in later
{character_name} has evolved!
// <<endCutscene>>     ← slot in later
===

title: Evolve_CuteCarrot
---
// <<startCutscene>>
Cute Carrot has appeared!
// <<endCutscene>>
===

title: Evolve_SpicyPepper
---
// <<startCutscene>>
Spicy Pepper has appeared!
// <<endCutscene>>
===
